# Speak Draft AI — Review Checklist

Run through this checklist before merging any PR or shipping a feature.

---

## ✅ Auth & Access Control

- [ ] All Convex mutations check `ctx.auth.getUserIdentity()` — unauthenticated requests throw
- [ ] Workspace isolation confirmed — no query returns data from another workspace
- [ ] Guest interview token validated on every request — expired or invalid tokens rejected
- [ ] Admin-only actions (billing, HubSpot connect, user management) gated by `role === "admin"`
- [ ] HubSpot OAuth tokens stored server-side only — never exposed to client

---

## ✅ Credit System

- [ ] Credit balance checked **before** starting interview or generating content
- [ ] Credits deducted via `internalMutation` only — never from client-callable functions
- [ ] Every deduction creates a `creditTransactions` ledger entry with `referenceId`
- [ ] Balance cannot go negative — action blocked, not retroactively charged
- [ ] Polar.sh webhook updates credit balance atomically — no double-credit on retry

---

## ✅ Interview Room

- [ ] Guest token is single-use — marked `in_progress` on first connection, blocks re-entry
- [ ] Token expiry enforced server-side (not just client-side)
- [ ] Deepgram WebSocket connection closes cleanly on interview end
- [ ] Audio stored to Cloudflare R2 — not in Convex
- [ ] Transcript saved to Convex only after interview marked `completed`
- [ ] No PII from guest (email, name) required — only optional
- [ ] Interview UI works without login — no Clerk session required on `/interview/[token]` route

---

## ✅ Content Generation

- [ ] Claude prompt includes: content type, topic, tone, language, keywords, outline, sources
- [ ] Output language explicitly stated in system prompt — not inferred
- [ ] Draft stored only after full generation — no partial saves
- [ ] Error state shown if generation fails — user can retry without re-interviewing
- [ ] Generated content does not include raw transcript — only synthesised output

---

## ✅ HubSpot Integration

- [ ] OAuth access tokens refreshed before API calls — handle 401 gracefully
- [ ] Content type correctly mapped to HubSpot API endpoint
- [ ] Bulk push handles rate limits — max 10 requests/second to HubSpot API
- [ ] Duplicate prevention — warn user if a draft with the same title already exists in portal
- [ ] `hubspotContentId` saved to draft on successful push
- [ ] HubSpot connection scoped to correct portal — agency multi-portal correctly isolated

---

## ✅ TypeScript & Code Quality

- [ ] No `any` types introduced
- [ ] No `console.log` left in production code — use Sentry for errors
- [ ] All new Convex tables have appropriate indexes
- [ ] Environment variables accessed via `process.env.VAR!` — validated at startup
- [ ] No secrets or API keys committed — all in `.env.local` / deployment env
- [ ] No TODO comments left unresolved in shipped code

---

## ✅ UI & UX

- [ ] Loading states on all async actions (brief save, interview start, generation, HubSpot push)
- [ ] Error states visible and actionable — not silent failures
- [ ] Mobile-responsive — especially the guest interview room (guests use phones)
- [ ] Language selector present on brief form — English default
- [ ] Credit balance visible in dashboard nav — always up to date via Convex reactive query
- [ ] Empty states handled — no broken UI when workspace has no briefs/drafts

---

## ✅ Performance

- [ ] Server Components used where no interactivity needed
- [ ] No unnecessary `useEffect` data fetching — prefer Convex `useQuery`
- [ ] Audio streaming uses WebSocket — no polling
- [ ] Cloudflare R2 signed URLs used for audio playback — not direct bucket URLs
- [ ] No N+1 queries in Convex — batch or index appropriately

---

## ✅ Before Going to Production

- [ ] Sentry DSN configured and errors flowing
- [ ] Polar.sh webhook secret validated on every webhook call
- [ ] Convex deployment environment set to production
- [ ] All HubSpot OAuth redirect URIs updated to production domain
- [ ] Resend sending domain verified
- [ ] R2 bucket CORS configured for production domain only
- [ ] Rate limiting on `/api/interview/*` routes — prevent abuse of guest links
